rlm-gar-search [-p PROJECT] NEEDLE

Search all DOCKER repositories in one or more Google Artifact
Registry projects for image names matching NEEDLE (substring).

Uses the Artifact Registry packages.list REST endpoint with
AIP-160 server-side filtering, so a single API call per repo is
enough — no client-side grep over every page of every repo. The
packages endpoint covers gcr.io-compatibility repos
(eu.gcr.io, gcr.io, us.gcr.io, asia.gcr.io) which Cloud Asset
Inventory does not index for Docker images.

Each matching package is printed as a fully qualified image path,
e.g. europe-docker.pkg.dev/PROJECT/REPO/PACKAGE.

ARGUMENTS
  NEEDLE      Substring to match against the package name. Required.

OPTIONS
  -p, --project PROJECT
              Restrict the search to a single GCP project. May be
              given more than once is not supported; use the env
              var for multiple projects.

  -h, --help  Print usage and exit.

ENVIRONMENT
  GAR_SEARCH_PROJECTS
              Colon-separated list of GCP project IDs to search
              when -p is omitted. One of -p or this variable is
              required; the function errors out if neither is set.

REQUIRES
  gcloud, jq, curl, python3 (for URL-decoding package names).

EXIT STATUS
  0   At least one match was found.
  1   No matches, or a required command / token was missing.
  2   Invalid arguments.
